Felx Fritsch:

"HyperSpace, a dApp in beta mode since February 2019, brands itself as protocol layer of a ‘New
Content Economy’ powered by an “attention economy model (...) designed to remove the middlemen
involved in content creation, distribution, and curation while enabling all value-creating parties
involved directly to benefit financially” (HyperSpace 2019). The platform organizes content in spaces
equivalent to groups on Facebook. Most of its decentralization efforts focus on providing flexible
governance tools to these spaces, thus supporting competitive differentiation and adaptation to
community needs in terms of self-administration and rewards structures."
(https://www.researchgate.net/publication/347390602_The_Common_Factory_Governance_and_Incentive_Systems_of_Blockchain-based_Social_Networks)

